#books-info-service

This API will provide the Books information .
Returns a successful response if bookId is present else will throw bad request with a message ' BookId does not exist'.

The project has below modules

main - This is the main class which starts our springboot application .

controller - The controller class will receive the incoming requests and acts as a resource class in providing the response. This
class  provides the information of all the books present in DB. This has been implemented by using spring JPA module. The books information 
is stored in the h2 database and the data is provided in the main class so that the data gets populated during start up of the service.

service - The service class calls the crudRepository to get teh books information using findAll and findById methods of JPA. will return the 
data if the id is present else will through bookInfoNotFoundException.

model - This is the POJO class which holds the properties of the java objects returned in the response.

configuration - This has configuration related to swagger, to provide the API contract details in web (swagger-ui.html) and in doc. the docket bean is defined in 
this class and all the methods in the controller class with /books uri will be provided with the contract details. 


exception - This has the global exception handler class so that the exceptions can be handled through out the application.  
